# 💎 FlowFi — Personal Finance Tracker

A full-stack personal finance web application built with **Python** and **Flask**.  
Track income, expenses, set budgets, and visualize your spending — all in one place.

> Built as part of the DekNek Full Stack Developer Internship assignment.



#Features

- 🔐 **User Authentication** — Signup, Login, Logout with secure password hashing
- 💸 **Transaction Management** — Add, Edit, Delete income and expense transactions
- 🔍 **Search & Filter** — Filter by month, type, category, or keyword
- 📊 **Dashboard** — Summary cards, bar charts, pie charts, and recent transactions
- 🎯 **Budget Goals** — Set monthly spending limits per category with progress tracking
- 📈 **Reports** — Yearly income vs expense trends, savings analysis, category breakdowns
- 💡 **Smart Insights** — Automatic tips based on your spending patterns
- 🗄️ **Database** — All data stored persistently per user

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

### Backend
| Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Python 3
| **Flask** | Web framework — routes, pages, REST API |
| **Flask-SQLAlchemy** | ORM — connects Python models to the database |
| **Flask-Bcrypt** | Secure password hashing |
| **Flask Sessions** | User authentication & login state management |
| **SQLite** | Local development database |
| **PostgreSQL** | Production database (via Supabase) |
| **Gunicorn** | WSGI production server for deployment |
| **python-dotenv** | Environment variable management |

### Frontend
| Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **HTML5** | Page structure and markup |
| **CSS3** | Custom styling — animations, glassmorphism, gradients |
| **Vanilla JavaScript** | Interactivity — API calls, modals, dynamic rendering |
| **Jinja2** | Flask's templating engine for dynamic HTML |
| **Chart.js** | Interactive bar, pie, doughnut, and line charts |
| **Google Fonts** | `Outfit` + `JetBrains Mono` typography |

# Deployment
**GitHub** Version control and source code 




# Project Structure

```
flowfi/
├── app.py                  # Main Flask app — all routes, models, API
├── requirements.txt        # Python dependencies
├── Procfile                # Render deployment config
├── .env.example            # Environment variable template
├── .gitignore
└── templates/
    ├── base.html           # Shared layout, sidebar, styles
    ├── login.html          # Login page
    ├── signup.html         # Signup page
    ├── dashboard.html      # Main dashboard with charts
    ├── transactions.html   # Transaction list with search & filters
    ├── budgets.html        # Budget goals with progress bars
    ├── reports.html        # Yearly reports & trends
    ├── tx_modal.html       # Add/Edit transaction modal (shared)
    └── tx_modal_js.html    # Modal JavaScript logic (shared)
```

